    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-08-05T03:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-08-05T03:00:00-05:00" n="173"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d173">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/11059: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-08-05T16:00:00+08:00"
                            >August 5, 1930—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received August 5—10:40 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>668. Legation’s 663, August 4, 11 a.m. The following from American Consul at
                    Hankow: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“August 4, 5 p.m. Substance of Adams’ August 3, 10 a.m. to
                                Washington:<note n="74" xml:id="d173fn74">See telegram No. 663,
                                August 4, 11 a.m., from the Minister in China, <ref target="#pg_161"
                                    >p. 161</ref>.</note> Advised [<hi rend="italic">Advice?</hi>]
                            to withdraw telegraphed to O’Shea, who is requested to notify other
                            Americans in Kanchow.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
